      java.lang.String FieldOrMethod.getClassName(ConstantPoolGen cpg)
      Deprecated. 
      If the instruction references an array class, this method will return "java.lang.Object". For code generated by Java 1.5, this answer is sometimes wrong (e.g., if the "clone()" method is called on an array). A better idea is to use the FieldOrMethod.getReferenceType(ConstantPoolGen) method, which correctly distinguishes between class types and array types.
